title: Allow also JS string and string[] where Git.Strarray is required
body:
Many functions require an argument of the type Git.Strarray, for example 
`static default(repo: Repository, target: Object, pathspecs: Strarray): Promise<number>;`

At the moment it is not possible to generate an instance of Strarray by hand,  `const p = new Strarray()` throws an error and there seems to be no other method to get such an instance.

Since nodegit allows the usage of string and string[] where Strarray is required (see [here](github.com/nodegit/nodegit/blob/master/test/tests/reset.js#L56), `filePath` is a string), I would also like to allow this in the type definitions.
nodegit seems to automatically convert JS string and string[] to Strarray internally if required.

I tried to make it slightly safer to use by providing a `type` for the static method, but I'm not sure if there _is_ a good way to express this correctly in TypeScript.
